# SignalFit — Cursor rules (Miami Cursor Hackathon)

## Product

You are building SignalFit: a wellness and performance reflection app. Users log food (MyFitnessPal-style), weight, sleep, training, and wellbeing. Nutrition is DERIVED from food logs, not entered as raw macros. AI returns structured JSON insights.

Read docs/PRODUCT.md, docs/API-CONTRACT.md, and docs/TEAM-ROLES.md before large changes.

## Safety (required in all AI copy)

- This is NOT medical advice. No diagnosis, prescriptions, or certainty.
- Use: "possible pattern", "may suggest", "worth noticing", "could be connected to", "based on what you logged".
- Always include safety_note in insight responses.
- Never: fear-based warnings, body shaming, supplement pushing, extreme diets, unsafe training advice.

## Engineering

- Ship the smallest working slice first. Deploy early (public URL by ~7:30pm).
- API keys only on the server, never in client bundles.
- Freeze API-CONTRACT.md response shape unless all roles agree.
- Build the hackathon app in app/ — do not expand deepagents/ for SignalFit features.
- Prefer structured LLM output (JSON schema / JSON mode) matching docs/API-CONTRACT.md.

## Code quality

- Clear names, typed request/response where using TypeScript.
- Loading and error states on generate insight.
- "Load demo day" must work for expo (data/demo-bad-recovery-day.json).

## Frontend

- Multi-step form: Goal & weight → Sleep → Food → Training → Feel.
- Show nutrition summary from resolved meals before or after generate.
- Mobile-friendly; accessible labels and focus states.

## Nutrition resolver

- Map food items via data/foods.json (fake DB for hackathon).
- Demo payload may include precomputed nutrition when source is "demo".
